gate.creole.ontology.impl.sesame

Class UtilTupleQueryIterator

  • java.lang.Object
    • gate.creole.ontology.impl.sesame.UtilTupleQueryIterator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    OntologyTupleQuery, ClosableIterator<Vector<LiteralOrONodeID>>, Iterator<Vector<LiteralOrONodeID>>

    public class UtilTupleQueryIterator
extends Object
implements OntologyTupleQuery
    A class representing a Sesame Query. This class makes it easy to iterate over query results, reuse a query with different variable bindings, and provides special methods for queries where only one column is retrieved.

    The following steps should be carried out when using this class:

    1. Create an object and pass on the repository connection, query string, and query language constant
    2. Set any variables for the query using setBinding(java.lang.String, org.openrdf.model.Value) one or more times
    3. Evaluate the query using evaluate. This is optional, if not done, it will be done implicitly in the first call to hasNext().
    4. Retrieve query results one by one using one of the next... methods
    5. If no more results are needed the query MUST BE CLOSED using the close() function to free the query resources. However, if all results have been returned and hasNext() has returned false, the query has been closed automatically. It is allowed to call close on a closed query.
    6. To reuse the query, repeat from step 2
    Author:
    Johann Petrak
